  "description": [
    "U S Childrens Bureau Writes a Book on Its First 25 Years Pamphlet Recites Achievements of Agency Which Was Unique When Created in 1912 by Borah Bill Anniversary to Be Cele brated at Mayflower Dinner Tonight What the U S Childrens Bureau has done since it was established in 1912 would fill a book Celebrating the Bureaus 25th an niversary 500 men and women will dine tonight at the Mayflower Mrs Roosevelt Labor Secretary Perkins Sen Borah and Grace Abbott head the list of speakers The Bureaus own anniversary con tribution is a 47page history of its oi igin and accomplishments A LARGE ORDER It was the worlds first public agency whose function was to con sider as a whole the conditions prob lems and welfare of childhood The law of April 9 1912 was a large order it required the new agency to investigate and report upon all mat ters pertaining to the welfare of children and child life among all classes of our people and especially investigate the questions of infant mortality the birth rate orphanages juvenile courts desertion dangerous occupations accidents and diseases of children employment legislation af fecting children in the several states and territories There"
